<title>PERU: Peru's Atacocha aims to slash workforce 30 percent.</title>
<headline>Peru's Atacocha aims to slash workforce 30 percent.</headline>
<dateline>LIMA 1997-05-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Peruvian polymetallic miner Minera Atacocha S.A. is requesting voluntary redundancies from 200 workers -- nearly a third of its workforce -- in a personnel reduction program, the Lima bolsa said Monday.</p>
<p>The stock market's daily report added that the program would be completed in May and will cost around $4 million in payments to workers who resign.</p>
<p>Atacocha, blue-chip on the maket, officials said the company currently employs 676 people.</p>
<p>((-- Lima newsroom, 511 221-2134))</p>
